        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 11 at 2:23PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 222 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles south of Gaffney, or 6 miles northeast of Pacolet Mills, moving
east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Draytonville, Thicketty, Saratt, Cherokee Falls, and Gaffney.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
